title: For Sale:  EXCELLENT Winchester Model 1873 - 44-40
postcontent: truly great and untouched example of an early Winchester Model 1873 rifle. Made in 1882, chambered in the highly desirable 44-40 WCF cartridge. 24" octagon barrel, full magazine.this sheet will be included with the gun. This is a 2nd model with all of the correct early features such as; A screwed on dust cover rail, visible trigger pin, and tang retention screws on the receiver sides. Also notice the lack of a caliber designation marking on the barrel and carrier block. The 38-40 and 32-20 were not introduced until later in the 1882-1883 period, all early 44 caliber rifles were not labeled "44 WCF" as this was the default caliber. This is a fine and untouched rifle with only honest wear. The receiver retains a lot of bright original bluing with some corner wear and old finish loss. The barrel and magazine tube have much of their original finish as well with the balance turned to an attractive plum patina.

title: For Sale:  CZ P-01
location: East Bend, Winston Salem, North Carolina
postcontent: DESCRIPTION The CZ P-01 is a compact, aluminum-framed 9mm designed for LE and Military duty, but its compact size and the reduced weight due to its forged alloy frame make it ideal for discrete carry as well. Equipped with a decocker, the P-01 provides convenience for those who prefer hammer-down carry. With a heavy first-round trigger pull, any additional shots are a light, crisp single action. The P-01 was the first CZ model to benefit from updated manufacturing technology at CZ’s Uhersky Brod factory. Since the time of its introduction (designed in 2001, NATO-approved in 2003) the production upgrades have been rolled out to the rest of the CZ 75 family and several new rifle models as well. These upgrades mean the components of the P-01/P-06 are completely interchangeable with every other P-01/P-06, with no individual fitting needed. This required some very careful re-design so that the reliability and accuracy were not impaired. With an integral 1913 accessory rail on its dust cover, the P-01 easily accepts any of the industry-standard lights and lasers to assist with low-light use. After 3 years of some of the most aggressive small arms testing ever, the CZ P-01 won the honor of replacing the CZ 75s previously used by the Czech National Police. Reliability:  The U.S. Army “Mean Rounds Between Failure” (MRBF) requirement is 495 rounds for 9mm pistols. During testing of the CZ P-01, the average number of stoppages was only 7 per 15,000 rounds fired. This is a .05% failure rate or an MRBF of 2142! title: For Sale/Trade:  Savage Striker 308 with scope

The gun was $700 when new. They usually sell for more than that on auction sites these days. In fact, they pop up on gunbroker about 1-2 times a year in 308, and sell for an average of $875 with no scope (last 5 years of ended auctions).  I have seen one go for as high as $1150 with no scope.  Still, by my calculator, Roughly an $1100 package.  Definately something you won't see often.Nearly all Savage bolt rifles have the same threading and barrel nut too, so you can take any old beat up woods gun, cut the barrel down, swap barrel and bolt face and change calibers. 308 strikers are pretty rare though.  Most 308 strikers are guns converted TO 308 and wont have the stainless barrel and muzzle break. Still fun as he'll though.
